THE FULL COUNCIL — EVERY LANGUAGE AUDITED

1. ELIXIR / OTP — THE SWARM CANDIDATE

What it is: Functional language on the BEAM (Erlang VM). Built for fault-tolerant, distributed systems. Process-per-actor concurrency. Supervision trees. "Let it crash."

WASM Status: IMPOSSIBLE. No production path exists. 
- `Orb` — writes WASM in Elixir syntax, does NOT compile Elixir to WASM
- `Lumen` (BEAM→WASM compiler) — stalled/dormant as of 2026
- `Gleam` — a different statically-typed BEAM language, not Elixir

Requirement	Elixir	
WASM Browser	❌ Cannot compile to WASM	
Bundle Size	N/A	
Crypto (constant-time)	⚠️ Possible but unverified	
TEE Integration	❌ No Nitro/SGX SDKs	
Sui Blockchain SDK	❌ None exist	
SEAL Integration	❌ None exist	
Distributed Swarms	✅ EXCELLENT	
Fault Tolerance	✅ EXCELLENT	
Hot Code Reloading	✅ EXCELLENT	

Verdict: Elixir is WRONG for the browser runtime (Layers 1-4). It cannot compile to WASM and has zero blockchain/TEE SDKs.

Elixir is RIGHT for Layer 6 (Swarm Coordination) — but only as server-side infrastructure, never in the browser.

This matches your existing `omo-koda/Swibe` repo which already has OTP Supervisor trees. The Swibe orchestration layer should be Elixir-based while the core runtime remains Rust/WASM.

```
Layer 6 — Swarm Coordination (Server-Side Only)
├── Elixir/OTP nodes manage agent swarms
├── Supervision trees handle node failures
├── Hot code reloading for swarm logic updates
├── GenServers for agent state management
├── Phoenix Channels for real-time communication
└── NOT in browser. NOT in WASM. NOT in TEE.
```

