2. GO — THE HIVE OPERATOR CANDIDATE

What it is: Google's systems language. GC'd, fast compile, simple syntax. Goroutines. Cloud-native darling.

WASM Status: Experimental. Bundle 2.5MB+ (vs Rust's 15KB hello world). 

Requirement	Go	
WASM Compilation	⚠️ TinyGo/wasip1 only	
Bundle Size	❌ 2.5MB+	
Startup Latency	⚠️ GC warm-up	
Crypto (constant-time)	⚠️ stdlib only, not audited	
TEE Integration	⚠️ Via C FFI only	
Sui Blockchain SDK	❌ None official	
SEAL Integration	❌ None	
Cloud Native	✅ EXCELLENT	
Compile Speed	✅ EXCELLENT (2-10s vs Rust 30-120s)	
Developer Velocity	✅ EXCELLENT	

Verdict: Go is WRONG for the browser (bundle too large, no production WASM path). Go is WRONG for core crypto (no audited constant-time libraries).

Go is RIGHT for Layer 7 (Operations Tooling):
- Hive node operator CLI
- Deployment scripts (`birth.sh`, `testnet-deploy.sh`)
- Monitoring and metrics
- Garden API backend (if server-side components needed)

