3. ZIG — THE LOW-LEVEL CANDIDATE

What it is: Systems language by Andrew Kelley. Manual memory management with guardrails. C equivalent. Lightning fast compile. Tiny binaries.

WASM Status: ✅ Supported natively via LLVM. Tiny bundles comparable to C. 

Requirement	Zig	
WASM Compilation	✅ Supported	
Bundle Size	✅ Tiny	
Startup Latency	✅ Instant (no GC)	
Crypto (constant-time)	⚠️ Via C libs only	
TEE Integration	❌ No native SDKs	
Sui Blockchain SDK	❌ None	
SEAL Integration	❌ None	
Memory Safety	⚠️ Manual (guardrails, not enforced)	
Ecosystem	❌ Very young	
Developer Pool	❌ Very small	

Verdict: Zig is WRONG for the core framework. No Sui ecosystem. No audited crypto. Manual memory management increases bug surface. Developer pool too small.

Zig is RIGHT only for future optimization (NOT v1):
- Ultra-low-level WASM intrinsics for crypto operations
- Embedded agent firmware (far future)
- C library bindings where Rust FFI is insufficient

